    "attributes": {
        "action": "Take action to ensure fair distribution of Afghan, Rohingya & Syrian Refugees",
        "additional_details": "Britain's duty is to uphold 70 year legacy of refugee protection. In 1951, the Refugee Convention agreed by the UN offered the right not to be sent back to a place of danger to all those with a \u201cwell-founded fear of persecution\u201d. I urge the UK Govt. to grant Refugee status to Afghan people & urging the G7 Govt. to make similar commitments. Canada, German & Bangladesh Govt. should be praised for their brave, humanitarian & compassionate approach taking unprecedented large numbers of refugees.",
        "background": "I urge the UK Govt. to commit to accept 50,000 Afghans and urging all Govt. to make similar commitments as the refugee problem is a matter of concern to the international community and must be addressed in the context of international cooperation and fairly sharing the burden.",
